"The China Children's Center will hold a series of events to let children experience 'high-tech' during the 'June 1st' Children's Day - Xinhua Net."
"The China Children's Center plans to hold a series of activities including the Children's Maker Experience, Children's Visual Arts Festival, and Family Book Carnival around the June 1st Children's Day, to let children experience the charm of cutting-edge technology," said the China Children's Center.
It is understood that the activities held by the China Children's Center during this year's June 1st Children's Day include the "Love Home Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival, the First Children's Visual Arts Festival, the "Book Carnival" activity, and the "Whole Family Loves Reading" Picture Book series."
The 'Love Home Cool' Children's Future Learning Carnival is the key activity of the China Children's Center to celebrate the June 1st Children's Day this year," Li Zhongming, Vice Director of the China Children's Center, introduced at the media briefing held on the 20th.
The activity focuses on the organic combination of social innovation and family creativity, and through children and family participation in various innovative education activities, making innovation practices become a cultural gene in families and making "hands-on" a new way of learning and living for families.
It is reported that the "Love Home Create Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival includes several dozens of cutting-edge technology experience contents, such as the "Bean Fruit Maker" experience activity, the Old Cow Children's Exploration Museum's anniversary celebration and the "Exploration Whole Family Love Children's Cute Over June 1st" activity, the VR National Experience Plan, and the "Maker Tribe" interactive workshop.